data.title: immaculate1895baptisms
data.text:
Transcribed from the original records on microfilm at Kenton County Public Library in Covington, KY. The originals are faded and difficult to read at times. Please verify with other sources or view the originals. I spelled the last names as the priest did. Note: Jacob & James were used interchangeably.

Rev. James McNerney, pastor of Immaculate Conception Church from the 1878-1915 on; must not have been a good record keeper. There are letters written many years after the fact that were testimonials about baptisms having taken place. Or corrections to the entries. These were mixed in with the baptisms.

Some of the baptisms for Oct/Nov 1898 had the baptismal dates obliterated at the edges of the page. Looks like the edges of the pages were torn.
